<subSubSection id="875C9A6E06B5AB64214DF995B50032EC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="DED042C5A117D5AD775940D2B786C64E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2FDFBE8F5B791B7646A122C84E48D8E2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Other six specimens collected by Jordan are preserved at LY, but they are not original material, since they are lacking a date or reporting dates later than the protologue.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B33ACC706F5CD47F640F418B57E2083C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The lectotype designated here matches the protologue and corresponds to the current application of the name, which is considered as a heterotypic synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="3F96D90E367999390E0F7AE71AF058D2" authority="subsp. sylvestris" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. sylvestris subsp. sylvestris" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subSpecies" species="sylvestris" subSpecies="sylvestris">D. sylvestris subsp. sylvestris</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="BFA1D4CDFCC1B8A3948700BF16909C59" author="Kerguelen, M" journalOrPublisher="Naturalia, Turriers" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B26" refString="Kerguelen, M, 1993. Index synonymique de la flore de France. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris." title="Index synonymique de la flore de France. Museum national d'histoire naturelle, Paris." year="1993">
<normalizedToken id="9D75BD679374E12590AA85DFFD871730" originalValue="Kerguélen">Kerguelen</normalizedToken>
(1993)
</bibRefCitation>
. The lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="BFB9CD0181915570429512888D0D078B" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. collivagus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="collivagus">
<emphasis id="A783550B708D5BA47F6ACFCF3F6CFAAF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. collivagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, concerning the shape of calyx teeth, is very similar to the lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="7C479DE23213A754F6EBA7A327DCDF86" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. inodorus" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="inodorus">
<emphasis id="761332230F6712D077CAC5921F482613" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. inodorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Gaertn., which in turn is currently included within the variability of 
<taxonomicName id="BE8852554124B8365B7BC8A0D271B127" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="D." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="D. sylvestris" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="sylvestris">
<emphasis id="52CE2D2589E9E09AB311F3880BE750F4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">D. sylvestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="A22F356F6624838B0B4D2C45A79CFB2D" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" author="Domina, G" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1096 - 1100" refId="B15" refString="Domina, G, Astuti, G, Barone, G, Gargano, D, Minuto, L, Varaldo, L, Peruzzi, L, 2021. Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae). Taxon 70 (5): 1096 - 1100, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" title="Lectotypification of the name Dianthus virgineus and consequences within the D. sylvestris group (Caryophyllaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1002/tax.12563" volume="70" year="2021">Domina et al. 2021</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
